        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(restart): add error logging to fire-and-forget restart emissions",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`emitPreparedGatewayRestart()` is async (returns a Promise) but called with `void` from `deferGatewayRestartUntilIdle()` and `armPendingRestartTimer()`, which are synchronous and cannot await it. Previously, any error during restart emission (e.g., failed IPC signal, broken supervisor connection) was silently lost — the gateway might fail to restart without any diagnostic.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Added `.catch()` with `restartLog.warn()` to all 7 `void emitPreparedGatewayRestart(...)` call sites\n- Each call site now logs errors to the restart subsystem logger\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Unit tests (60/60 passed):**\n```\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  60 passed (60)\n```\n\n**Before fix:**\n```typescript\nvoid emitPreparedGatewayRestart(opts.emitHooks, opts.reason);\n// Any error silently lost\n```\n\n**After fix:**\n```typescript\nvoid emitPreparedGatewayRestart(opts.emitHooks, opts.reason)\n  .catch((emitErr: unknown) => {\n    restartLog.warn(`restart emission failed: ${String(emitErr)}`);\n  });\n// Errors now logged via restart subsystem logger\n```\n\n**Affected call sites (7 total):**\n- `armPendingRestartTimer` — scheduled restart after deferral timeout (1 site)\n- `deferGatewayRestartUntilIdle` — direct call and 4 polling branches (5 sites)\n- `emitGatewayRestart` fallback — plain restart emit (1 site)\n\n## Review\n- Manually reviewed and verified\n- AI-assisted: Yes",
